Adds conditional JSON resource loading via the JSON. Conditions can be registered via ResourceConditions#register.
Here is an example:
```javascript
{
  "type": "fabric:mod",
  "condition": {
    "minecraft": ">=1.16.3",
    "yes": [
      "<1.0.0",
      ">=2.0.0"
    ]
  }
}
```

The above JSON can be put in a file named `<original file>.fabricmeta` to apply to individual files or `.fabricmeta` to apply to the whole folder.

